    "body": "update: \r\n\r\nSuper annoying issue: accidentally marked a contract as abstract in solidity, then instantiated it with   \r\nconst factory = await ethers.getContractFactory(\"MockERC20\");\r\nlet erc20: ERC20 = (await factory.deploy(initialHolder, initialTokens, name, symbol)) as ERC20;\r\n(which was allowed!)\r\n\r\nthen called balanceOf on it and got the error message: \"Error: call exception (address=\"0xf4e77E5Da47AC3125140c470c71cBca77B5c638c\", method=\"balanceOf(address)\", args=[\"0x2fFd013AaA7B5a7DA93336C2251075202b33FB2B\"], version=4.0.47)\"\r\n\r\ntook me way longer than I'd like to admit to figure out..\r\n\r\ntakeaway is should there be an earlier warning for instantiating an abstract contract?\r\n\r\n\r\n```\r\nmacosx 10.15.4\r\nnode v11.15.0\r\n{\r\n    \"dependencies\": {\r\n      \"@nomiclabs/buidler\": \"^1.3.3\",\r\n      \"@nomiclabs/buidler-ethers\": \"^1.3.3\",\r\n      \"@nomiclabs/buidler-etherscan\": \"^1.3.3\",\r\n      \"@nomiclabs/buidler-truffle5\": \"^1.3.3\",\r\n      \"@nomiclabs/buidler-waffle\": \"1.3.4\",\r\n      \"@nomiclabs/buidler-web3\": \"^1.3.3\",\r\n      \"@openzeppelin/contracts\": \"^3.0.1\",\r\n      \"@studydefi/money-legos\": \"^2.2.1\",\r\n      \"@types/chai\": \"^4.2.11\",\r\n      \"@types/mocha\": \"^7.0.2\",\r\n      \"@types/node\": \"^14.0.1\",\r\n      \"@uniswap/v2-core\": \"^1.0.0\",\r\n      \"@uniswap/v2-periphery\": \"^1.0.0-beta.0\",\r\n      \"buidler-typechain\": \"^0.0.5\",\r\n      \"chai\": \"^4.2.0\",\r\n      \"ethereum-waffle\": \"2.5.1\",\r\n      \"ethers\": \"^4.0.23\",\r\n      \"lodash\": \"^4.17.15\",\r\n      \"solidity-cli\": \"^1.0.3\",\r\n      \"solidity-coverage\": \"^0.7.5\",\r\n      \"ts-generator\": \"^0.0.8\",\r\n      \"ts-node\": \"^8.10.1\",\r\n      \"typechain\": \"^1.0.3\",\r\n      \"typechain-target-ethers\": \"^1.0.4\",\r\n      \"typechain-target-truffle\": \"^1.0.2\",\r\n      \"typechain-target-web3-v1\": \"^1.0.4\",\r\n      \"typescript\": \"^3.9.2\"